            "Why did God destroy the animals in the flood, if it was human beings who had sinned?",
            "[A teaching of R’ Yehoshua ben Qorchah] [answers this question with a parable:] A man made a wedding for his son, preparing a feast.  When his son died, “he stood and destroyed his [son’s] wedding canopy.  He said: For nothing else did I make the canopy except for my son. Now that he has died, what [use is it] for me?   So said the Holy One:  For nothing else did I create the beasts and animals except for the sake of humanity. Now that humanity is sinning, what [use are they] for me?”"
